seed_chunks:
Cold salvage lanes are policed by **Helix Meridian**, the “safety-first” corporate consortium that issues contracts, tags derelicts, and pays bounties—while quietly scrubbing evidence of black-site boardings and buying back survivors’ silence. Opposing them in the open is the **Freejack Union**, a loose coalition of salvage crews preaching mutual aid and fair shares, but secretly trafficking restricted logs and alien-grade components to fund a coming strike-war. Between them moves the **Vesper Choir**, a fringe disaster-relief sect that offers grief counseling and clean-air canisters on dock… and covertly hunts specific wrecks to recover something “singing” in the hulls. Helix hires Rhea’s kind to crush Freejack leaks; Freejack feeds her rumors; the Choir turns both into bait.

```json
{
  "factions": [
    {
      "name": "Helix Meridian Consortium",
      "public_front": "Corporate salvage licensing, safety audits, hazard pay, and derelict claim arbitration across deep-space lanes.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Maintain a network of black-site boarding actions and evidence erasure; retrieve or destroy logs tying executives to the classified incident."
    },
    {
      "name": "Freejack Union",
      "public_front": "Independent crews’ mutual-aid network advocating fair splits, rescue protocols, and protection from corporate predation.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Smuggle restricted telemetry, weapons, and exotic salvage to bankroll an organized revolt and expose Helix—selectively."
    },
    {
      "name": "Vesper Choir",
      "public_front": "Dockside relief sect providing counseling, funerary rites, and filtration supplies to traumatized spacers.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Track anomalous derelicts and recover a transmissible ‘signal’/artifact; manipulate crews into opening sealed compartments."
    }
  ]
}
```

